Uses of Package
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design

Packages that use edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design The design package has all the classes necessary to represent XDL designs in RapidSmith. 
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design.explorer   
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design.parser The design.parser package is a parser for XDL and populates the classes found in the design package. 
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device The device package represents all of the resources available on an FPGA device (part name, tiles, primitive sites and routing resources). 
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.router This package contains a basic router and structure to help users build routers of their own. 
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util The util package contains several classes aimed at helping RapidSmith users do a variety of operations such as install RapidSmith, convert files, and run certain Xilinx tools from within RapidSmith. 
 

Classes in edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design used by edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design
Attribute
          The Attribute object in XDL is used in several places, Design, Instance, Net and Module.
Design
          The design class houses an entire XDL design or hard macro.
Instance
          This class represents the inst object in XDL design files.
Module
          This class represents the modules as found in XDL.
ModuleInstance
          There is no direct representation of a module instance in XDL.
Net
          This class represents the nets in XDL.
NetType
          This enum is simply a way to check net types easier than using Strings.
Pin
          This class represents the sources and sinks found in net declarations (inpins and outpins)
PIP
          This class represents the programmable-interconnect-points (PIPs) as found in XDL designs.
Port
          This class represents the ports used to define the interfaces of modules in XDL.
